242
00:12:54,162 --> 00:12:57,966
[ Man ] We Don't
Want Her Here! We Don't Need
No Coloreds In This School!

243
00:12:58,000 --> 00:13:00,770
Listen To What We're Saying!
This Is Our School!

244
00:13:00,803 --> 00:13:04,574
[ Woman ]
Take Her Back To The Colored
School Where She Belongs!

245
00:13:04,607 --> 00:13:08,310
[ Shouting Continues ]

246
00:13:08,343 --> 00:13:10,146
Let's Go, Baby.

247
00:13:13,848 --> 00:13:17,085
Two, Four, Six, Eight!
We Don't Wanna Integrate!

248
00:13:17,118 --> 00:13:19,622
Back Off! Back Off!

249
00:13:33,835 --> 00:13:36,671
Two, Four, Six, Eight!
We Don't Wanna Integrate!

250
00:13:36,704 --> 00:13:39,742
This Way, Mrs. Bridges.

251
00:13:36,704 --> 00:13:39,742
[ Woman ]
What Is Goin' On?

252
00:13:43,811 --> 00:13:47,048
I Can't Believe
They're Sending
That Little Negro Here.

253
00:13:47,082 --> 00:13:51,721
- Miss Woodmere? This Is
Ruby Bridges And Her Mother.
- You Girls Get Back.

254
00:13:51,753 --> 00:13:54,089
[ Woman ]
...Sittin' Next To My Kid!

255
00:13:51,753 --> 00:13:54,089
What Are We Gonna Do!

256
00:13:54,122 --> 00:13:56,124
Take My Child
Outta Here.

257
00:13:56,157 --> 00:13:59,061
[ Rotary Dial Clicking ]

258
00:14:02,231 --> 00:14:04,801
That's Real Good, Honey.

259
00:14:06,167 --> 00:14:08,169
Come On, Boy.
Come On!

260
00:14:08,203 --> 00:14:10,805
Mrs. Ridley,
What Are You Doin'?

261
00:14:10,838 --> 00:14:12,175
Go-- Go Back
To Your Coloring.

262
00:14:14,376 --> 00:14:15,944
[ Woman ]
It Ain't Gonna Happen.

263
00:14:15,978 --> 00:14:18,146
My Child Ain't Gonna Sit
With Their Kind.

264
00:14:18,180 --> 00:14:19,348
It Ain't Gonna Happen!

265
00:14:19,381 --> 00:14:21,217
[ Miss Woodmere ] This Is The
Administrative Vice Principal

266
00:14:21,250 --> 00:14:23,419
At William Franz.
Superintendant Redmond, Please.

267
00:14:23,452 --> 00:14:26,956
My Kid Ain't Going
To School With No Jigaboo.

268
00:14:29,857 --> 00:14:31,926
Mama?

269
00:14:31,959 --> 00:14:35,296
Where's The Other Girls
Who Were Supposed To
Come With Me?

270
00:14:35,329 --> 00:14:38,401
[ Miss Woodmere ]
I Didn't Know For Sure
It Was Going To Be Here.

271
00:14:38,434 --> 00:14:40,002
What About The Other Children?

272
00:14:40,035 --> 00:14:41,404
They Told Me
There Was Two More

273
00:14:41,436 --> 00:14:43,104
Supposed To Be Comin'
To School With Ruby Nelle.

274
00:14:43,137 --> 00:14:45,107
Well, I Suppose Their Parents
Had The Good Sense

275
00:14:45,140 --> 00:14:46,475
Not To Put Their Children
Through This.

276
00:14:46,507 --> 00:14:50,378
[ Door Closes ]

277
00:14:46,507 --> 00:14:50,378
Would You-- Hello?
Tell Him To Call Miss Woodmere.

278
00:14:50,411 --> 00:14:52,714
Miss Woodmere,
This Here Woman Says

279
00:14:52,747 --> 00:14:54,717
She's The New Teacher
Supposed To Be Here.

280
00:14:54,750 --> 00:14:56,886
She Don't Look Like
No Teacher, Though.

281
00:15:00,723 --> 00:15:04,226
Yes, Can I Help You?

282
00:15:00,723 --> 00:15:04,226
Yes. Good Morning.
I'm Barbara Henry.

283
00:15:04,258 --> 00:15:07,862
Uh, Superintendent Redmond
Told Me To Report The Principal
For Work Today.

284
00:15:07,896 --> 00:15:11,132
Oh, Not Today.
Not Today.

285
00:15:11,165 --> 00:15:16,405
Well, She's In A Board Meetin'
Downtown And It's, It's Just
Not Sorted Out Just Yet.

286
00:15:16,438 --> 00:15:18,441
Come Back Tomorrow.
Mm-Hmm.

287
00:15:16,438 --> 00:15:18,441
Okay.

288
00:15:23,344 --> 00:15:26,915
[ Water Running ]

289
00:15:34,923 --> 00:15:37,893
[ Woman Whispering ]
She's Gonna Use Our Washroom.

290
00:15:37,925 --> 00:15:39,929
[ Door Closes ]

291
00:15:37,925 --> 00:15:39,929
That Ain't Right.

292
00:15:49,304 --> 00:15:53,809
You Sure You Don't Want
Somethin' To Drink, Honey?

293
00:15:53,842 --> 00:15:55,812
No, Mama.

294
00:16:15,396 --> 00:16:17,934
[ Bell Ringing ]

295
00:16:23,104 --> 00:16:25,741
She Is Dismissed.

296
00:16:27,476 --> 00:16:29,979
Come On, Baby.
Let's Go.

297
00:16:33,281 --> 00:16:35,785
This School Is Easy,
Mama.

298
00:16:45,828 --> 00:16:47,829
<I>[ Man On Tape Recorder ] With
Children In Crisis Situations,

299
00:16:45,828 --> 00:16:47,829
Hey!

300
00:16:47,862 --> 00:16:49,898
<I> Stress Seems To Present
Itself In A Variety Of Ways.

301
00:16:49,931 --> 00:16:51,399
Hi, Sweetie. What Happened?
Did It End Early?

302
00:16:51,433 --> 00:16:53,068
I Never Got There.
The Streets Were Blocked.

303
00:16:53,101 --> 00:16:55,838
You're Never Gonna Believe
Why. It Was Crazy.

304
00:16:55,871 --> 00:16:57,273
I'm, Uh, Sitting
In The Car, Right?

305
00:16:57,305 --> 00:17:00,108
There's Police
Everywhere. I Can't Move.

306
00:17:00,141 --> 00:17:01,276
And There's
This Crowd Of Women

307
00:17:01,309 --> 00:17:02,277
Standing In Front
Of A School.

308
00:17:02,310 --> 00:17:04,279
Then This Little, Tiny,
Adorable Negro Girl

309
00:17:04,313 --> 00:17:07,016
Gets Out Of A Car
Surrounded By Huge Marshals.

310
00:17:07,048 --> 00:17:08,950
And Then These Women--

311
00:17:08,984 --> 00:17:10,486
I'm Pretty Sure
They're Mothers--

312
00:17:10,518 --> 00:17:13,189
They, They Start Chanting
These, These Hateful Things

313
00:17:13,221 --> 00:17:14,556
At This Little, Bitty Girl.

314
00:17:14,590 --> 00:17:17,560
I've Never Seen
Anything Like It.

315
00:17:17,593 --> 00:17:19,995
People Can Be
So Mean, Bob.

316
00:17:17,593 --> 00:17:19,995
Yeah.

317
00:17:20,027 --> 00:17:23,097
I Grew Up Watching How
They Treated Effie, My Nanny.

318
00:17:23,131 --> 00:17:27,169
They'd Act Like Her Color
Made Her Guilty Of Something.

319
00:17:27,201 --> 00:17:31,172
Maybe I Could Work With Her.
You Know, Offer My Help
To Her And Her Family.

320
00:17:31,206 --> 00:17:33,909
And Study The Situation
And Try To Help Her Cope.

321
00:17:33,941 --> 00:17:36,010
I Think It Would Certainly
Be As Important

322
00:17:36,044 --> 00:17:38,380
As The Work I Did With
The Kids In The Polio Ward.

323
00:17:38,412 --> 00:17:41,383
- I Think It's A Great Idea.
- Yeah?

324
00:17:44,218 --> 00:17:46,255
[ Crowd Shouting ]

325
00:17:46,287 --> 00:17:50,124
Two, Four, Six, Eight!
We Don't Wanna Integrate!

326
00:17:50,158 --> 00:17:53,563
[ Chanting Continues ]

327
00:17:50,158 --> 00:17:53,563
Get These People Back.

328
00:17:55,330 --> 00:17:59,135
[ Butler ]
Wait A Minute, Mrs. Bridges.

329
00:17:55,330 --> 00:17:59,135
[ Crowd Pounding On Car ]

330
00:18:06,941 --> 00:18:10,179
Clear The Way. Okay.
Okay, Mrs. Bridges.

331
00:18:10,211 --> 00:18:12,247
Come On, Ruby.

332
00:18:15,616 --> 00:18:20,055
[ Cop ]
All Right Now, Keep It Clear!
Get Back! Get Back!

333
00:18:20,087 --> 00:18:22,490
Two, Four, Six, Eight!
We Don't Wanna Integrate!

334
00:18:22,524 --> 00:18:24,994
[ Chanting Continues ]

335
00:18:22,524 --> 00:18:24,994
Don't Mind Them, Ruby.
Keep Walking.

336
00:18:26,561 --> 00:18:28,530
[ Man ]
Get Back, You Scum.

337
00:18:28,563 --> 00:18:32,001
Two, Four, Six, Eight!
We Don't Wanna Integrate!

338
00:18:32,034 --> 00:18:34,469
Two, Four, Six, Eight!
We Don't Wa--

339
00:18:39,240 --> 00:18:41,910
This Is Your Teacher,
Mrs. Henry.

340
00:18:43,545 --> 00:18:45,680
[ Phone Ringing ]

341
00:18:45,714 --> 00:18:48,050
Well, Hello, Ruby Nelle.

342
00:18:48,083 --> 00:18:50,119
It's So Nice To Meet You.

343
00:18:52,219 --> 00:18:54,422
Very Nice To Meet You Too,
Mrs. Bridges.

344
00:18:54,456 --> 00:18:57,259
Likewise.

345
00:18:57,292 --> 00:19:01,362
So, Ruby, I Hear That
You're Quite A Good Student.

346
00:19:01,395 --> 00:19:03,598
Is That True?

347
00:19:01,395 --> 00:19:03,598
Yes, Ma'am.

348
00:19:03,632 --> 00:19:06,936
Well, That's Perfect 'Cause
I'm Pretty Good Myself.

349
00:19:08,003 --> 00:19:11,640
[ Woman Clicks Tongue ]
I Don't Know.

350
00:19:11,672 --> 00:19:14,209
[ Crowd Chanting ]

351
00:19:18,479 --> 00:19:22,617
This Here Is The
Captain Doctor Robert Coles.

352
00:19:25,019 --> 00:19:26,988
Pleased To Meet You,
Captain.

353
00:19:25,019 --> 00:19:26,988
Pleasure.

354
00:19:27,022 --> 00:19:29,625
Sorry, But I Have To Check
Everyone That Comes In Here.

355
00:19:27,022 --> 00:19:29,625
I Understand.

356
00:19:29,658 --> 00:19:31,627
Would You Turn Around,
Please?

357
00:19:29,658 --> 00:19:31,627
Sure.

358
00:19:35,663 --> 00:19:39,501
[ Crowd Shouting ]

359
00:19:35,663 --> 00:19:39,501
There Was A Phonics Book
In Here Just A Minute Ago.

360
00:19:42,070 --> 00:19:44,306
[ Woman ]
Get Out Now!

361
00:19:42,070 --> 00:19:44,306
You'll Have To Forgive Me. I--

362
00:19:44,339 --> 00:19:47,343
I Haven't Quite Gotten
My Bearings Yet.

363
00:19:47,375 --> 00:19:50,645
How Long Have You Been Here?

364
00:19:47,375 --> 00:19:50,645
Since 8:30.

365
00:19:52,680 --> 00:19:56,151
[ Woman ]
Go Home, You Pickaninny!
You Don't Belong Here!

366
00:19:56,183 --> 00:19:58,253
[ Shouting Continues ]

367
00:20:11,033 --> 00:20:13,468
[ Shouting Continues,
Muted ]

368
00:20:13,501 --> 00:20:16,137
The Humidity Here
Is Something.

369
00:20:16,170 --> 00:20:19,475
Where You From?

370
00:20:16,170 --> 00:20:19,475
Boston, Originally.

371
00:20:19,507 --> 00:20:23,545
But I've Been Teaching Children
Overseas On A Military Base.

372
00:20:23,577 --> 00:20:25,381
I Just Recently Was Married,

373
00:20:25,413 --> 00:20:27,348
And My Husband's Work
Is Here In New Orleans,

374
00:20:27,382 --> 00:20:30,419
So I've Come
To Join Him.

375
00:20:30,451 --> 00:20:32,587
Well, Welcome To The South.

376
00:20:32,621 --> 00:20:35,291
Yeah.

377
00:20:39,693 --> 00:20:41,430
Well, I'm Here Today
Because I'd Like To Talk

378
00:20:41,462 --> 00:20:44,365
To The Negro Child Who's
Attending Here And, Uh--

379
00:20:44,399 --> 00:20:47,636
Now What Would You Wanna Talk
To That Little Nigra For?

380
00:20:48,769 --> 00:20:51,573
I'd Like To See
How She's Doing.

381
00:20:51,605 --> 00:20:56,344
The Focus Of My Work
Is To Study How
Children Handle Stress.

382
00:20:56,378 --> 00:20:59,381
How They Cope With Crisis
Intrigues Me.

383
00:20:56,378 --> 00:20:59,381
I Can Tell You Right Now

384
00:20:59,413 --> 00:21:02,718
There's Nothin' Intriguing
About That Colored Child.

385
00:21:05,554 --> 00:21:08,157
I Certainly Respect
Your Opinion, Ma'am.

386
00:21:08,189 --> 00:21:10,592
Um--

387
00:21:10,624 --> 00:21:12,760
But, Uh,
If You Would Allow Me

388
00:21:12,794 --> 00:21:16,265
To Speak To Her Mother,
I'd Appreciate It.

389
00:21:18,299 --> 00:21:21,136
I Can't Get More Involved
Than I'm Required To.

390
00:21:25,640 --> 00:21:28,611
Maybe You Could
Give Me The Child's Name.

391
00:21:30,378 --> 00:21:33,215
We Have Strict Orders.

392
00:21:33,247 --> 00:21:36,251
I'd Be Breakin' The Law.

393
00:21:43,257 --> 00:21:46,127
Well, If You're So Interested
In The Colored,

394
00:21:46,160 --> 00:21:48,863
You Ought To Go
Talk To Their Organization.

395
00:21:48,897 --> 00:21:50,499
I'm Sorry.
What Organization?

396
00:21:50,532 --> 00:21:53,135
That Colored People's
Organization.

397
00:21:55,437 --> 00:21:57,406
Good Day.

398
00:22:00,674 --> 00:22:04,180
[ Barbara ]
Okay, I'm Gonna Write
A Word On Your Paper.

399
00:22:07,282 --> 00:22:10,252
Christmas!

400
00:22:07,282 --> 00:22:10,252
Very Good.

401
00:22:10,285 --> 00:22:13,488
Now, Listen.
Using The Letters
In Christmas,

402
00:22:13,522 --> 00:22:17,159
I Want You To Write Down
As Many Words As You Can,

403
00:22:17,191 --> 00:22:20,595
Using Only The Letters
In The Word.

404
00:22:20,629 --> 00:22:22,631
Okay?

405
00:22:22,663 --> 00:22:27,635
[ Indistinct Shouting ]

406
00:22:27,669 --> 00:22:31,239
C-H-

407
00:22:31,273 --> 00:22:34,776
R-I-

408
00:22:34,808 --> 00:22:37,812
S-T!

409
00:22:37,845 --> 00:22:40,681
Christ!

410
00:22:40,715 --> 00:22:43,752
Her Dexterity
Is Advanced For This Age.

411
00:22:43,785 --> 00:22:46,822
She Writes Fast And Well.

412
00:22:46,854 --> 00:22:50,159
[ Cielle ]
She Picks Up Everything,
Just Like A Sponge.

413
00:22:50,191 --> 00:22:53,795
C-A-R. Car.

414
00:22:55,564 --> 00:22:59,901
H-I-T. Hit.

415
00:22:59,935 --> 00:23:05,674
S-I-T. Sit.

416
00:23:05,707 --> 00:23:11,513
H-I-M. Him.

417
00:23:11,545 --> 00:23:16,919
S-T-A-R. Star.

418
00:23:24,292 --> 00:23:27,629
Excuse Me.
Can You Tell Me
Where The Lounge Is?

419
00:23:27,661 --> 00:23:31,400
Please?

420
00:23:27,661 --> 00:23:31,400
This Way.

421
00:23:31,432 --> 00:23:34,435
You Know, I Don't Envy You,
Mrs. Henry.

422
00:23:34,468 --> 00:23:37,372
You Must Have
Really Needed A Job.

423
00:23:37,404 --> 00:23:40,475
[ Laughing ]

424
00:23:37,404 --> 00:23:40,475
Did You See That Dress
She Was Wearin'?

425
00:23:41,942 --> 00:23:45,346
There's No Need For
Consolation, Miss Spencer.

426
00:23:45,380 --> 00:23:47,748
I've Taught Children From
Many Different Backgrounds,

427
00:23:47,782 --> 00:23:49,285
And I Enjoy Them All.

428
00:23:50,285 --> 00:23:53,255
This Is A Disgrace.

429
00:23:53,287 --> 00:23:55,990
This Place Is Ruined.

430
00:23:56,024 --> 00:23:59,395
And You're Part Of It.

431
00:24:03,664 --> 00:24:05,700
Well, It's Unfortunate
That She Feels That Way.

432
00:24:05,734 --> 00:24:07,636
Frankly, I Think
It's Pretty Silly

433
00:24:07,669 --> 00:24:11,372
For A Whole School To Empty Out
Because Of One Little Girl.

434
00:24:11,405 --> 00:24:13,774
When Superintendent Redmond
Offered Me This Position,

435
00:24:13,807 --> 00:24:16,444
I Had No Idea
I'd Have One Student.

436
00:24:16,478 --> 00:24:19,948
I-I Told Miss Woodmere
I Couldn't Teach
That Little Negress.

437
00:24:19,980 --> 00:24:23,986
We Have Friends That
Gave Their Resignation
Rather Than Teach Her.

438
00:24:24,018 --> 00:24:25,953
[ Sighs ]

439
00:24:25,987 --> 00:24:29,891
For What We Are About To Receive
May We Truly Be Thankful. Amen.

440
00:24:29,923 --> 00:24:33,561
'Round Here,
We Don't Teach Them,

441
00:24:33,594 --> 00:24:36,231
And Our Kids Don't
Learn With 'Em.

442
00:24:47,609 --> 00:24:50,846
[ Crowd Shouting ]
Black Trash, Don't Come Back!
Black Trash, Don't Come Back!

443
00:24:50,879 --> 00:24:54,616
Black Trash, Don't Come Back!
Black Trash, Don't Come Back!

444
00:24:54,649 --> 00:24:58,053
Black Trash, Don't Come Back!
Black Trash, Don't Come Back!

445
00:24:58,085 --> 00:25:00,256
♪ [ Indistinct Singing ]

446
00:24:58,085 --> 00:25:00,256
Black Trash, Don't Come Back!

447
00:25:01,823 --> 00:25:04,392
This Is Dangerous,
Lucielle.

448
00:25:04,426 --> 00:25:08,063
It's Only Day Two.
It Ain't Too Late
To Back Out Of This.

449
00:25:08,095 --> 00:25:10,632
Why Are You Always
Scared Of Everything, Huh?

450
00:25:10,664 --> 00:25:12,401
Never Wanna Make No Waves.

451
00:25:12,433 --> 00:25:14,535
The Only Way We Gonna
Have Something

452
00:25:14,568 --> 00:25:15,836
Is If We Take It.

453
00:25:14,568 --> 00:25:15,836
I Fought In A War
And I Won A Medal.

454
00:25:15,870 --> 00:25:19,507
You Think I Got That Medal
Bein' Scared?

455
00:25:19,541 --> 00:25:22,811
Hon, You Best Mind
Who You Talkin' To.

456
00:25:22,843 --> 00:25:24,846
I'm Sorry.

457
00:25:26,413 --> 00:25:27,648
Baby,
I've Been To The School,

458
00:25:27,681 --> 00:25:29,383
And I've Seen It. It's Better.

459
00:25:29,417 --> 00:25:31,520
It's Cleaner.
It's Nicer. It's Newer.

460
00:25:31,553 --> 00:25:33,789
And Her Teacher.
Her Teacher's From Up North,

461
00:25:33,822 --> 00:25:35,056
And She's Smart,
And She's Kind.

462
00:25:35,090 --> 00:25:37,659
She's Supposed To
Go Alone Tomorrow.

463
00:25:37,691 --> 00:25:38,859
Now,
She's Just A Little Girl.

464
00:25:38,892 --> 00:25:40,528
How Can We Put Her
Through That?

465
00:25:40,562 --> 00:25:41,796
I'm Sick Of People
Telling Us

466
00:25:41,830 --> 00:25:44,066
Where We Can't Go,
What We Can't Do,

467
00:25:44,099 --> 00:25:46,068
What We Ain't
Supposed To Have.

468
00:25:46,101 --> 00:25:50,972
My Children
Are Gonna Have More.
They Deserve More.

469
00:25:51,005 --> 00:25:53,675
And The Only Way Things Are
Gonna Get Better For Them

470
00:25:53,708 --> 00:25:57,045
Is If We Make 'Em Better.

471
00:25:57,077 --> 00:26:01,083
Honey,
We Can't Be Afraid.

472
00:26:02,516 --> 00:26:05,554
Give Mama Some Sugar.

473
00:26:05,586 --> 00:26:07,555
Give Mama A Kiss.

474
00:26:07,589 --> 00:26:09,558
[ Murmuring ]

475
00:26:07,589 --> 00:26:09,558
Good Night, Baby.

476
00:26:10,958 --> 00:26:13,728
[ Girl ]
Good Night, Mom.

477
00:26:13,762 --> 00:26:16,498
You Know Mama's Gotta
Go Back To Work Tomorrow.

478
00:26:16,530 --> 00:26:19,400
And Daddy's Working.

479
00:26:19,433 --> 00:26:21,068
So You Think You Could
Be A Brave Girl

480
00:26:21,102 --> 00:26:24,406
And Go To School By Yourself
With The Big Men?

481
00:26:33,180 --> 00:26:35,816
Hmm?

482
00:26:33,180 --> 00:26:35,816
Okay.

483
00:26:35,850 --> 00:26:37,986
[ Sighs ]

484
00:26:38,018 --> 00:26:41,155
You Know Jesus
Faced A Mob Too, Baby.

485
00:26:41,189 --> 00:26:43,824
Just Like You.

486
00:26:43,858 --> 00:26:46,462
And You Know What He Did?

487
00:26:47,762 --> 00:26:50,999
