Okay.

733
00:42:20,994 --> 00:42:24,399
[ Humming ]

734
00:42:39,146 --> 00:42:42,615
I Wanna Draw
My Teacher Now.

735
00:42:42,648 --> 00:42:45,418
Why Don't You Wanna
Finish This One?

736
00:42:45,452 --> 00:42:47,921
It Is Finished.

737
00:42:47,954 --> 00:42:51,726
Are These The People
Out In Front Of The School?

738
00:42:51,758 --> 00:42:56,963
Is That How They Look To You?

739
00:42:51,758 --> 00:42:56,963
I Don't Know How They Look
'Cause I Don't Look At 'Em.

740
00:42:56,996 --> 00:43:01,935
Why Don't You Look At Them?

741
00:42:56,996 --> 00:43:01,935
'Cause My Mama And The Man
Told Me Not To,

742
00:43:01,968 --> 00:43:04,405
So I Don't.

743
00:43:04,438 --> 00:43:07,575
Me And Mrs. Henry Count High
When We Do Jumping Jacks.

744
00:43:07,608 --> 00:43:10,410
All The Way
To A Hundred.

745
00:43:10,443 --> 00:43:13,747
[ Humming ]

746
00:43:13,780 --> 00:43:15,449
They Were Just Lovely.

747
00:43:15,481 --> 00:43:17,817
Next Time You Should Really
Sit Down And Chat With Them.

748
00:43:17,851 --> 00:43:22,757
You Know, Jane, I'm Not
There To Socialize. Okay?

749
00:43:22,789 --> 00:43:24,758
[ Sighs ]

750
00:43:27,561 --> 00:43:29,729
So How Did It Go
In There?

751
00:43:29,762 --> 00:43:32,532
Oh. According To Ruby,
Everything's Just Fine
At School.

752
00:43:32,566 --> 00:43:35,936
She's Having A Good Time.

753
00:43:32,566 --> 00:43:35,936
Well, Maybe--

754
00:43:35,968 --> 00:43:39,572
I Mean, How Can That Be?
It Doesn't Make Any Sense.

755
00:43:39,606 --> 00:43:44,879
She Doesn't Show Any Signs Of
Being Scared Or Traumatized.

756
00:43:44,912 --> 00:43:46,914
Honey, You'll Figure It Out.

757
00:43:46,947 --> 00:43:50,418
- It's The First Meeting.
- Mm-Hmm.

758
00:43:50,450 --> 00:43:55,822
[ Crowd Shouting ]

759
00:43:50,450 --> 00:43:55,822
[ Woman ] Go Home!
We Don't Want You Here!

760
00:43:55,856 --> 00:43:59,627
- I'm Gonna Poison You!
- Black, Black,
Don't Come Back!

761
00:43:59,659 --> 00:44:02,529
- [ Chanting Continues ]
- Don't Look, Ruby.

762
00:44:08,769 --> 00:44:13,541
We're Gonna Poison You!
We're Gonna Poison You
Till You Choke To Death!

763
00:44:13,574 --> 00:44:15,575
[ Sobbing ]

764
00:44:23,983 --> 00:44:27,988
What's The Matter, Baby?

765
00:44:23,983 --> 00:44:27,988
[ Sniffs ]
I'm Scared.

766
00:44:30,523 --> 00:44:33,026
Did You Have
A Bad Dream?

767
00:44:33,059 --> 00:44:37,465
No, But I Was
Thinking Bad Things.

768
00:44:37,497 --> 00:44:39,532
Mmm.

769
00:44:39,566 --> 00:44:41,535
Did You Say
Your Prayers?

770
00:44:45,137 --> 00:44:49,075
Well, What Do You Expect,
Honey? Come On.

771
00:44:50,510 --> 00:44:52,512
Come On.

772
00:44:54,814 --> 00:44:58,519
I Want You To Go In There,
Get Back On Your Knees,

773
00:44:58,552 --> 00:45:03,090
And You Ask Him
To Take Care Of It.

774
00:45:03,122 --> 00:45:05,159
I'm Scared.

775
00:45:09,530 --> 00:45:10,631
Go On.

776
00:45:43,863 --> 00:45:46,233
Thank You, Mrs. Stein.

777
00:45:46,266 --> 00:45:48,802
[ Indistinct ]

778
00:45:46,266 --> 00:45:48,802
Hey.

779
00:45:48,834 --> 00:45:51,238
It's That Colored Girl.

780
00:45:48,834 --> 00:45:51,238
[ Doorbell Jangling ]

781
00:45:55,342 --> 00:45:58,244
Hi, Mrs. Stein.

782
00:45:55,342 --> 00:45:58,244
Hi.

783
00:45:58,278 --> 00:46:02,283
I'm So Sorry, Abon,
But Will You Please...

784
00:46:02,316 --> 00:46:06,954
Not Come Here Anymore?

785
00:46:06,987 --> 00:46:09,856
Why?

786
00:46:06,987 --> 00:46:09,856
Please.

787
00:46:09,889 --> 00:46:11,858
Please, Just Go.

788
00:46:16,863 --> 00:46:19,667
Okay, Fine.
Won't Come In Here No More,

789
00:46:19,700 --> 00:46:23,737
If That's How You Want It.

790
00:46:23,769 --> 00:46:25,805
You Remember Who Was First
To Come In Here

791
00:46:25,838 --> 00:46:27,840
When You First Moved Here

792
00:46:27,874 --> 00:46:30,010
And Them Crackers
Wouldn't Buy From No Jews.

793
00:46:30,043 --> 00:46:32,046
Ain't Never Been Nothin'
But Nice To You, Ma'am,

794
00:46:32,079 --> 00:46:34,615
But If That's How You Want It,
That's How It's Gonna Be.

795
00:46:34,648 --> 00:46:37,684
Come On.

796
00:46:37,717 --> 00:46:40,186
Come On.

797
00:46:40,220 --> 00:46:45,660
[ Doorbell Jangling ]

798
00:46:47,126 --> 00:46:49,762
[ Mocking Humming ]

799
00:46:49,796 --> 00:46:51,766
[ Abon ]
Come On, Y'all.
Let's Go.

800
00:46:52,798 --> 00:46:55,268
Let's Go.
Get Ready For Bed.

801
00:46:55,302 --> 00:46:59,139
Come On. Ruby Nelle,
You Better Eat That Food.

802
00:46:59,171 --> 00:47:00,740
[ Cielle ] Child, You
Better Finish That Plate

803
00:47:00,773 --> 00:47:01,976
And Stop
That Foolishness.

804
00:47:02,008 --> 00:47:03,876
I'm Just Not Hungry.

805
00:47:03,909 --> 00:47:05,612
You Heard Your Daddy.

806
00:47:07,280 --> 00:47:12,353
Baby, Please.
Please Eat Something.

807
00:47:12,385 --> 00:47:16,824
Maybe I'll Have Some Chips
Out Of The Bag.

808
00:47:16,856 --> 00:47:19,860
Only A New Bag, Though.

809
00:47:19,892 --> 00:47:22,896
And A "Co-Cola."

810
00:47:27,034 --> 00:47:29,003
[ Sighs ]

811
00:47:41,447 --> 00:47:43,750
Here, Swallow This.

812
00:47:48,155 --> 00:47:51,725
My Cookin' That Bad,
All You Want To Eat
Is Packaged Foods?

813
00:47:51,758 --> 00:47:54,695
You Didn't Eat Nothin'
Yesterday. You Didn't
Eat Nothin' This Mornin'.

814
00:47:54,728 --> 00:47:56,729
All You Wanna Eat
Is Chips.

815
00:47:56,762 --> 00:48:00,400
Does Mrs. Stein
Stand Outside My School

816
00:48:00,434 --> 00:48:03,303
And Say Those Mean Things?

817
00:48:00,434 --> 00:48:03,303
[ Sighs ]

818
00:48:03,336 --> 00:48:07,741
No. Baby, She's Jewish.
They Not Much Nicer
To Her, Either.

819
00:48:07,773 --> 00:48:12,145
But She Said We Can't
Come In Her Store No More.

820
00:48:12,179 --> 00:48:14,314
She Did?

821
00:48:15,347 --> 00:48:17,750
Well, That's
Not Very Nice, But--

822
00:48:17,784 --> 00:48:19,952
It's Because Of Me, Right?

823
00:48:19,985 --> 00:48:22,889
How Come No One
Likes Me, Mama?

824
00:48:24,090 --> 00:48:27,661
No. Baby, No.
No.

825
00:48:30,831 --> 00:48:32,399
See, You And The Other
Colored Girls

826
00:48:32,432 --> 00:48:35,235
Are Doin' Something
That White Folks Don't Like.

827
00:48:35,267 --> 00:48:40,474
It's Not You. They Don't
Want Colored Children
Goin' To Their Schools.

828
00:48:40,507 --> 00:48:44,378
But You Know What?
You're Special,
And You're Smart,

829
00:48:44,410 --> 00:48:48,282
And You Deserve An Education
Just As Good As Theirs.

830
00:48:48,314 --> 00:48:49,849
They Say Those Mean Things

831
00:48:49,883 --> 00:48:52,753
'Cause They Want You To Think
That You Don't Deserve It.

832
00:48:52,785 --> 00:48:57,758
But No Matter What They Say,
You Know God Loves You.

833
00:48:57,791 --> 00:49:00,394
And They Don't Know
What They're Talking About.

834
00:49:02,262 --> 00:49:06,432
[ Crowd Shouting ]

835
00:49:06,465 --> 00:49:08,835
- Go Home!
- [ Shouting Continues ]

836
00:49:08,869 --> 00:49:10,771
I'm Gonna Poison You.
I'm Gonna Poison You

837
00:49:10,804 --> 00:49:12,472
Till You Choke To Death,
You Little Nigger!

838
00:49:12,505 --> 00:49:15,842
- Don't Look, Ruby.
- Go Home! Go Home!

839
00:49:15,876 --> 00:49:19,146
Step Back!
Get Her Inside!

840
00:49:19,179 --> 00:49:22,282
Step Back!

841
00:49:19,179 --> 00:49:22,282
Yes, Sir! I Got You!

842
00:49:22,314 --> 00:49:25,218
- I-I'm Just Tryin' To Take
My Daughter To School.
- Traitor!

843
00:49:25,251 --> 00:49:27,520
[ Shouting ]

844
00:49:27,554 --> 00:49:29,889
Okay, Reverend.
Come On. Hurry Up.

845
00:49:29,923 --> 00:49:32,993
[ Girl Whimpering ]

846
00:49:29,923 --> 00:49:32,993
Come On. Hurry Up.
Let's Get Outta Here.

847
00:49:33,025 --> 00:49:35,729
Traitor! Traitor! Traitor!

848
00:49:41,066 --> 00:49:43,070
[ Sobbing ]

849
00:49:41,066 --> 00:49:43,070
They're Crazy.

850
00:49:44,871 --> 00:49:48,508
Traitor!
Why Don't You Go Home?
We Don't Want You Here!

851
00:49:50,177 --> 00:49:53,213
- Go Home!
- Traitor!

852
00:49:54,481 --> 00:49:55,883
Honey,

853
00:49:55,916 --> 00:49:58,151
Some People Were Raised
With Funny Ideas

854
00:49:58,184 --> 00:50:00,353
About People That Are
Different Than Them.

855
00:50:03,122 --> 00:50:06,260
You See, They--
[ Sighs ]

856
00:50:06,293 --> 00:50:09,262
They Think Skin Color
Is Everything.

857
00:50:09,296 --> 00:50:11,431
And If You Don't Have
The Same Skin As Theirs,

858
00:50:11,463 --> 00:50:13,166
They Don't Like You.

859
00:50:13,200 --> 00:50:15,202
Oh.

860
00:50:18,338 --> 00:50:21,542
Not All People
Are Like That.

861
00:50:21,575 --> 00:50:24,144
We're Not Like That.

862
00:50:24,177 --> 00:50:28,382
We Know That All People
Are Special.

863
00:50:28,414 --> 00:50:30,983
And That We Should
Respect Everyone.

864
00:50:31,017 --> 00:50:32,987
Is It Only My Skin?

865
00:50:34,954 --> 00:50:37,824
[ Sighs ]

866
00:50:37,858 --> 00:50:40,894
Ruby, Do You Know What,
What Slavery Is?

867
00:50:42,028 --> 00:50:44,497
No? Well, There Was
A Time In The South

868
00:50:44,530 --> 00:50:49,369
When White People
Used To Own Negroes.

869
00:50:49,401 --> 00:50:54,240
Like You Would Own
A Pet Or, Or A Toy.

870
00:50:54,273 --> 00:50:58,244
And They Used To Make
The Negroes Work Very Hard
Without Any Pay.

871
00:51:01,313 --> 00:51:03,483
But In The North,
Where I'm From,

872
00:51:04,950 --> 00:51:07,286
We Knew That Was Wrong.

873
00:51:07,320 --> 00:51:11,425
And The North And South
Had A Big Fight,
And The North Won.

874
00:51:11,458 --> 00:51:15,162
And They Told The South
They They Had To
Free All The Slaves.

875
00:51:15,195 --> 00:51:19,566
Praise The Lord.

876
00:51:15,195 --> 00:51:19,566
[ Chuckles ]

877
00:51:19,599 --> 00:51:21,901
But You See, Some People
Still Haven't Gotten Over

878
00:51:21,934 --> 00:51:26,472
The Difference
Between Negro And White,

879
00:51:26,505 --> 00:51:29,175
And They Don't Want Them
To Be Together.

880
00:51:31,077 --> 00:51:33,914
And Those People Outside
Are Angry

881
00:51:33,947 --> 00:51:36,215
Because The Laws
Are Forcing The Whites

882
00:51:36,249 --> 00:51:38,352
To Be With The Negroes,
And They Don't Like That.

883
00:51:39,952 --> 00:51:42,922
But Why Do They Say
Those Mean Things To Me?

884
00:51:42,956 --> 00:51:45,626
I Didn't Do Anything.

885
00:51:49,095 --> 00:51:52,499
No, You Didn't
Do Anything, Honey.

886
00:51:55,467 --> 00:51:58,504
You See, They Just--

887
00:51:58,537 --> 00:52:03,644
They Just Feel Threatened
And-- [ Sighs ]

888
00:52:03,677 --> 00:52:07,981
They're So Angry That
They Don't Like Anybody,
Not Even Themselves.

889
00:52:09,715 --> 00:52:14,186
You Know, Some People
Sometimes When They
Feel Kicked Down That--

890
00:52:14,220 --> 00:52:15,689
Hey Don't Know
How To Do Anything Else

891
00:52:15,722 --> 00:52:18,926
But Kick Other People Down.

892
00:52:18,959 --> 00:52:21,495
And You And I Both Know
That That's Not Right.

893
00:52:21,528 --> 00:52:24,031
Right? Yeah.

894
00:52:26,099 --> 00:52:28,102
Okay.

895
00:52:53,994 --> 00:52:56,963
[ Baby Crying ]

896
00:52:56,996 --> 00:52:59,732
Why Don't We Take A Look
At Our Drawings Now?

897
00:52:59,766 --> 00:53:02,468
Shall We? Let's See
What You've Done.

898
00:53:04,237 --> 00:53:07,340
Hmm.
Let Me See That.

899
00:53:07,374 --> 00:53:10,410
- Is This You Here, Ruby?
- Uh-Uh.

900
00:53:10,443 --> 00:53:12,412
It's My Friend Alison
And Her Daddy.

901
00:53:12,445 --> 00:53:16,182
She's Sad Because He Don't
Like Her To Play With No One

902
00:53:16,215 --> 00:53:20,487
Whose Daddy Doesn't
Make As Much Money
As Her Daddy Makes.

903
00:53:20,519 --> 00:53:25,756
Oh. So Alison's
A White Girl.

904
00:53:24,791 --> 00:53:26,994
No.

905
00:53:24,791 --> 00:53:26,994
No?

906
00:53:27,026 --> 00:53:30,731
She's Like Me.

907
00:53:27,026 --> 00:53:30,731
Oh? I Couldn't Tell

908
00:53:30,764 --> 00:53:32,632
Because You Draw Her
And Her Father

909
00:53:32,664 --> 00:53:36,035
With Pink Crayons
Instead Of Brown.

910
00:53:36,068 --> 00:53:40,539
In Fact, You Draw Yourself
With Pink Crayons A Lot Too.

911
00:53:40,572 --> 00:53:44,577
So You've Got Blue Hair
Instead Of Black.

912
00:53:44,610 --> 00:53:48,014
And, Um, You've Drawn Yourself

913
00:53:48,048 --> 00:53:50,250
And Alison And Her Father
With Missing Parts.

914
00:53:50,282 --> 00:53:52,585
See, You Don't Have
A Mouth There,

915
00:53:52,619 --> 00:53:54,421
Alison Doesn't Have Ears,

916
00:53:54,454 --> 00:53:57,524
And Her Father Has No Eyes.

917
00:53:57,557 --> 00:54:00,293
But You Teacher And I--
You've Drawn Us

918
00:54:00,325 --> 00:54:03,130
With All Of Our Parts
Carefully Intact.

919
00:54:04,463 --> 00:54:07,166
Why Do You Think
That Is?

920
00:54:14,273 --> 00:54:16,575
You Call This Good?

921
00:54:16,608 --> 00:54:20,079
There's Kindergartners
Who Draw Better Than That.

922
00:54:20,113 --> 00:54:22,349
[ Laughing ]

923
00:54:20,113 --> 00:54:22,349
[ Laughing ]

924
00:54:22,382 --> 00:54:24,351
What's Wrong
With My Drawing?

925
00:54:24,383 --> 00:54:26,686
[ Laughing ]

926
00:54:26,718 --> 00:54:28,688
Yeah, That Is
Pretty Bad, Huh?

927
00:54:30,289 --> 00:54:32,558
[ Laughing ]

928
00:54:30,289 --> 00:54:32,558
That's Good.
[ Laughing ]

929
00:54:33,860 --> 00:54:35,829
Oh.

930
00:54:33,860 --> 00:54:35,829
Oh, Bob.

931
00:54:35,862 --> 00:54:39,166
You've Gotta Try This.
Lucielle Taught Me
How To Make Red Beans And Rice.

932
00:54:39,199 --> 00:54:42,269
[ Laughs ]
Uh, No, Thank You.

933
00:54:42,302 --> 00:54:45,738
[ Kids ] Good Night, Daddy.

934
00:54:42,302 --> 00:54:45,738
He Never Gets Anything
This Good At Home.

935
00:54:45,771 --> 00:54:47,740
Everyone In Bed?

936
00:54:45,771 --> 00:54:47,740
Yeah.

937
00:54:47,773 --> 00:54:49,775
[ Clears Throat ]
Why Don't You Have
A Seat, Doc?

938
00:54:49,809 --> 00:54:52,211
Oh, Uh, No.
No, Thank You.

939
00:54:52,244 --> 00:54:54,547
It's Kind Of You,
But We Really Need
To Hit The Road.

940
00:54:54,581 --> 00:54:57,584
Oh. Well, At Least
Let Me Give You Some Pie.

941
00:54:57,617 --> 00:54:59,586
I Mean, Biloxi Is A Long Way.

942
00:54:59,619 --> 00:55:01,621
Uh, No. I'm Not Hungry.
Really.

943
00:55:01,653 --> 00:55:05,756
Uh, I Should Tell You,
Though, Before We Go

944
00:55:04,791 --> 00:55:07,327
That I'm A Bit
Concerned About Ruby

945
00:55:07,360 --> 00:55:09,362
And What's Going On
Out At The School.

946
00:55:09,394 --> 00:55:12,364
Have Either Of You Noticed
Any Peculiar Behavior
With Ruby, Uh,

947
00:55:12,398 --> 00:55:16,870
Aside From The Doll And How
She Spoke To Her Siblings?

948
00:55:16,903 --> 00:55:21,675
[ Abon Sighs ]
Uh, No, No. She, Uh,
Seems All Right To Me.

949
00:55:22,642 --> 00:55:25,612
She Won't Eat
Like She Used To.

950
00:55:25,644 --> 00:55:27,213
Doctor, Let Me Tell You
Something.

951
00:55:27,246 --> 00:55:28,681
She Don't Want Nothin'
'Cept Packaged Food.

952
00:55:28,715 --> 00:55:30,483
Like Cookies And Chips,

953
00:55:30,517 --> 00:55:33,687
And... She Won't Drink
Nothin' But Coca-Cola.

954
00:55:36,755 --> 00:55:41,260
Um, I Think I Know
What's Happening.

955
00:55:41,293 --> 00:55:44,530
I've Observed The Hecklers
Out In Front Of The School,

956
00:55:44,563 --> 00:55:49,802
And There's
One Particular Woman Who--

957
00:55:49,836 --> 00:55:52,473
Well, She...

958
00:55:54,807 --> 00:55:56,877
Threatens To Poison Ruby.

959
00:55:56,909 --> 00:55:59,245
I'm Sorry Very Much
To Have To Tell You Both,

960
00:55:59,278 --> 00:56:01,614
But She Threatens
To Kill Her.

961
00:56:01,648 --> 00:56:03,617
[ Gasps ]
Oh.

962
00:56:03,650 --> 00:56:05,119
What?

963
00:56:07,320 --> 00:56:09,588
Excuse Me.

964
00:56:09,621 --> 00:56:12,625
I'm Sorry, Mr. Bridges.
I Am.

965
00:56:09,621 --> 00:56:12,625
Ain't Your Fault.

966
00:56:12,659 --> 00:56:15,795
[ Lucielle Crying ]

967
00:56:12,659 --> 00:56:15,795
You Gotta Show
Yourselves Out. I Gotta--

968
00:56:15,827 --> 00:56:18,664
Of Course. Yeah.
Good Night.

969
00:56:22,936 --> 00:56:25,805
[ Crying Continues ]

970
00:56:39,218 --> 00:56:43,557
How Can They Be So Cruel
To My Baby?

971
00:56:43,590 --> 00:56:47,526
I Thought I Was Doing
The Right Thing.
I Really Did.

972
00:56:47,559 --> 00:56:50,596
Shh. Come On. Come On.

973
00:56:50,630 --> 00:56:52,398
It Ain't All Your Fault.

974
00:56:52,432 --> 00:56:53,867
I Should
Have Put My Foot Down.

975
00:56:53,900 --> 00:56:56,369
I Shouldn't Have Let You
Talk Me Into It.

976
00:56:56,401 --> 00:56:59,872
I Ain't Never Been For This
In The First Place.

977
00:56:59,905 --> 00:57:02,241
So You Think
We Should Stop?

978
00:57:02,275 --> 00:57:05,345
Ruby Ain't Stayin'
In That School, Cielle.

979
00:57:07,780 --> 00:57:09,950
I Just Need To Pray
About This.

980
00:57:09,983 --> 00:57:13,353
I Know My God Wouldn't Give Me
More Than We Could Handle.

981
00:57:14,621 --> 00:57:17,757
He--

982
00:57:17,789 --> 00:57:19,391
What Do You Think
You're Doin'?

983
00:57:19,425 --> 00:57:21,461
I'm Doin' What's Best
For Our Daughter.

984
00:57:22,595 --> 00:57:24,798
I Watched Her Tonight,

985
00:57:24,831 --> 00:57:27,534
And I Listened
And I See She--

986
00:57:27,566 --> 00:57:28,767
She Got It In Her Head

987
00:57:28,800 --> 00:57:31,304
That White Folks
Is Better Than Colored.

988
00:57:32,671 --> 00:57:34,641
She Draws Colored Folk
Deformed

989
00:57:34,673 --> 00:57:36,543
And White Folk Perfect.

990
00:57:39,778 --> 00:57:42,648
But What's That Got To Do
With Jesus?

991
00:57:45,684 --> 00:57:50,724
[ Whispering ]
Ain't Nobody Really Know
What He Looks Like.

992
00:57:50,757 --> 00:57:54,961
But When She
Sees This Every Day,

993
00:57:54,994 --> 00:57:57,264
Tells Her That God
Looks More Like
Them White Folks

994
00:57:57,296 --> 00:58:00,300
Outside Her School
Than Her.

995
00:58:06,905 --> 00:58:08,374
[ Sighs ]

996
00:58:08,407 --> 00:58:09,976
Can You Make Some Dinner
Now, Please?

997
00:58:10,008 --> 00:58:13,780
Oh, So You're Hungry,
Huh?

998
00:58:10,008 --> 00:58:13,780
Yes.

999
00:58:13,813 --> 00:58:15,981
Oh, Well, I'm Not.

1000
00:58:16,014 --> 00:58:18,717
I Had
A Home-Cooked Meal.

1001
00:58:18,751 --> 00:58:20,720
Good Night.

1002
00:58:23,822 --> 00:58:26,525
[ Groans ]

1003
00:58:26,559 --> 00:58:29,595
Daddy! Daddy!
I Have To Show
You Something!

1004
00:58:29,628 --> 00:58:32,731
All Right.
Hold On.

1005
00:58:32,764 --> 00:58:35,668
[ Sighs ]
Ah, Report Card.

1006
00:58:43,108 --> 00:58:48,414
Arithmetic, "A".
Readin', "A".

1007
00:58:48,447 --> 00:58:51,450
Spellin', "A".

1008
00:58:51,483 --> 00:58:54,953
Music, "A".

1009
00:58:54,987 --> 00:58:57,923
Art, "A".

1010
00:58:57,956 --> 00:59:00,726
All A's, Daddy!

1011
00:58:57,956 --> 00:59:00,726
Yeah.

1012
00:59:00,760 --> 00:59:04,464
I See.
That's Great, Baby.
That's--

1013
00:59:04,496 --> 00:59:07,433
That's A--

1014
00:59:10,836 --> 00:59:12,838
You Like Your New School,
Don't Ya?

1015
00:59:15,742 --> 00:59:20,580
Yeah, I'm--
I'm Glad You Do.

1016
00:59:25,385 --> 00:59:28,755
Go-- Go Get Changed,
And, Uh, Go Play.

1017
00:59:28,787 --> 00:59:30,824
Mary And Carl Waitin'
For Ya Up The Street.

1018
00:59:48,608 --> 00:59:51,577
Hi, Jimmy,
We Goin' In!

1019
00:59:48,608 --> 00:59:51,577
Hi, Scott!

1020
00:59:51,610 --> 00:59:54,146
Traitor!
Tra-- Jimmy!

1021
00:59:54,179 --> 00:59:56,582
Hey, Scott,
Wait Up!

1022
00:59:54,179 --> 00:59:56,582
Jimmy! Come Back Here, Boy!

1023
00:59:56,615 --> 00:59:58,485
No, I Wanna Go
To School, Ma!

1024
00:59:58,517 --> 01:00:00,586
Jimmy! Jimmy!

1025
01:00:00,619 --> 01:00:03,088
Scott, I'm Comin' Too!

1026
01:00:03,121 --> 01:00:05,090
Now, Ruby, You Was With Me
At The Supermarket

1027
01:00:05,124 --> 01:00:08,061
When I Bought That Rice
And Those Beans.

1028
01:00:08,093 --> 01:00:10,896
You Saw They Was
Wrapped Tight.

1029
01:00:10,929 --> 01:00:13,666
No One's Put
Nothin' In There.

1030
01:00:15,066 --> 01:00:18,771
Ruby, Baby,
You've Got To Eat!
You Hear Me?

1031
01:00:24,510 --> 01:00:25,745
Good Girl.

1032
01:00:25,778 --> 01:00:26,879
Mama,

1033
01:00:26,912 --> 01:00:30,016
You Said Those People
Outside My School Would Stop.

1034
01:00:30,048 --> 01:00:32,718
They Will, Honey.

1035
01:00:32,751 --> 01:00:35,020
They Will!

1036
01:00:32,751 --> 01:00:35,020
When?

1037
01:00:41,593 --> 01:00:44,097
You Know, Ruby,
When You Feel Like This,

1038
01:00:44,130 --> 01:00:47,599
You Gotta Remember,
Just Turn Unto The Lord.

1039
01:00:47,633 --> 01:00:52,071
Remember What
I Told You
Jesus Did?

1040
01:00:52,104 --> 01:00:54,207
They Can't
Hurt You, Honey.

1041
01:00:54,240 --> 01:00:57,910
Those Men Are There
To Protect You.

1042
01:00:57,943 --> 01:01:01,213
And Remember,
God Loves You!

1043
01:01:01,246 --> 01:01:04,817
[ Kissing Sound ]
Mmm.

1044
01:01:01,246 --> 01:01:04,817
[ Abon ] Cielle.

1045
01:01:04,851 --> 01:01:07,186
Hey!

1046
01:01:04,851 --> 01:01:07,186
Hi!

1047
01:01:07,220 --> 01:01:10,757
Hello! Got Some Goodies
For You.

1048
01:01:07,220 --> 01:01:10,757
Hey, Alma!

1049
01:01:10,789 --> 01:01:14,460
Good To See You.
Oh, Thank You!
What Can I Get You Two?

1050
01:01:14,494 --> 01:01:17,130
Oh, Nothing. Thank You.

1051
01:01:14,494 --> 01:01:17,130
Jus' Some Coffee, Darlin'.

1052
01:01:17,162 --> 01:01:19,166
But Let Me Help.

1053
01:01:20,999 --> 01:01:24,704
Ooh,
It's Pretty!

1054
01:01:24,737 --> 01:01:27,106
I Want It!

1055
01:01:24,737 --> 01:01:27,106
No.
It's Mine!

1056
01:01:27,139 --> 01:01:31,110
Ruby Nelle, Not Everything
Comes In This House
Is For You.

1057
01:01:31,142 --> 01:01:33,979
[ Alma Chuckling ]

1058
01:01:31,142 --> 01:01:33,979
Now, You Gonna
Have To Share!

1059
01:01:34,012 --> 01:01:37,217
Oh, My. Would Y'all
Like To Adopt
A Couple Of Kids?

1060
01:01:37,249 --> 01:01:39,718
Actually, We'd Love
To Have Ruby Spend A Day

1061
01:01:39,751 --> 01:01:43,222
With Our Girl Sometime,
If That's All Right.

1062
01:01:39,751 --> 01:01:43,222
[ Ruby ] Ooh!

1063
01:01:43,255 --> 01:01:45,591
Oh, I'm Sure
She Would Love That!

1064
01:01:45,624 --> 01:01:47,693
Honey, We've Got A Piano,

1065
01:01:47,726 --> 01:01:49,561
And My Wife Would Like
To Teach You To Play.

1066
01:01:49,595 --> 01:01:51,564
Would You Like That?

1067
01:01:51,597 --> 01:01:53,999
Oh, My. You Have
Your Very Own Piano?

1068
01:01:54,032 --> 01:01:56,702
You Know,
She's Been Learnin'
A Bit With Miss Henry.

1069
01:01:56,735 --> 01:01:59,104
Well, We Just Want
To Spend Some Time
With Her.

1070
01:01:59,137 --> 01:02:01,974
- Let Her Know
We're Here For Her.
- [ Scoffs ]

1071
01:02:02,008 --> 01:02:04,945
[ Paper Shuffling ]

1072
01:02:06,144 --> 01:02:09,081
I Gotta Get Me
Some Air.

1073
01:02:09,115 --> 01:02:11,084
[ Door Slams ]

1074
01:02:13,285 --> 01:02:17,824
I'm Sorry.
He's Havin' A Hard Time.

1075
01:02:17,856 --> 01:02:19,224
I Understand.

1076
01:02:19,258 --> 01:02:23,263
What He's Goin' Through Has
Got To Be Hard On Any Man.

1077
01:02:24,863 --> 01:02:29,068
Abon! Abon!

1078
01:02:34,005 --> 01:02:35,941
[ Sighs ]
Honey, I Know
You Don't Believe Me,

1079
01:02:35,974 --> 01:02:38,710
But I Really Think They
Do Mean Well.

1080
01:02:38,744 --> 01:02:41,713
[ Scoffs ]
Please, Those People
Ain't Interested In Ruby.

1081
01:02:41,746 --> 01:02:43,181
Yes, They Are Too!

1082
01:02:43,215 --> 01:02:44,851
And I Think
It Will Be A Good Idea

1083
01:02:44,883 --> 01:02:46,186
For Her
To See How They Live.

1084
01:02:46,218 --> 01:02:50,590
Show Her What Our Folks
Can Have When They Have
A Good Education.

1085
01:02:50,622 --> 01:02:52,626
They Were Just
Being Polite.

1086
01:02:54,726 --> 01:02:58,564
But Not Polite Enough
To Invite Us, Huh?

1087
01:02:58,597 --> 01:03:04,237
You Know, Tell Me.
Did Alma Broyard Invite You
To Tea? Oh, No.

1088
01:03:04,269 --> 01:03:06,305
No! Why?

1089
01:03:06,338 --> 01:03:10,242
Well, Their--
Their Little Visits
Every Once In A While,

1090
01:03:10,275 --> 01:03:13,211
Having Ruby To Their House
And-- And Showin' Her
How They Live--

1091
01:03:13,244 --> 01:03:15,213
That Ain't Gonna Help
This Family!

1092
01:03:15,246 --> 01:03:17,716
Huh?
Where Are The Broyards

1093
01:03:17,749 --> 01:03:20,353
When My Daughter Ain't
Eatin' And When She's
Havin' Nightmares?

1094
01:03:20,385 --> 01:03:22,588
They Don't Wanna Know
About All That!

1095
01:03:22,621 --> 01:03:25,991
They Don't Want
To Support Us Like
Real Friends!

1096
01:03:26,025 --> 01:03:29,829
And You--
You Just-- You Just Smile
And Just Suckin' It Up!

1097
01:03:29,862 --> 01:03:31,831
That's Enough, Abon!

1098
01:03:31,863 --> 01:03:35,867
There's Nothing Wrong
With Me Wantin' Ruby To See
Another Side Of Life!

1099
01:03:35,900 --> 01:03:39,004
I Want Her To Learn
To Play The Piano,
If She Wants To.

1100
01:03:39,037 --> 01:03:41,373
I Want Her To Experience

1101
01:03:41,407 --> 01:03:45,711
Being In A Nice House...
Without Havin' To Clean It.

1102
01:03:45,744 --> 01:03:49,081
I Don't Wanna See
My Daughter Being Used,

1103
01:03:49,115 --> 01:03:53,086
No More... By Nobody.

1104
01:03:53,119 --> 01:03:55,689
[ Sobs ]

1105
01:03:57,255 --> 01:03:59,224
[ Man ]
Hey, Charlie!

1106
01:04:07,767 --> 01:04:09,736
Hey, Abon!

1107
01:04:09,769 --> 01:04:14,240
How's It Goin'?

1108
01:04:09,769 --> 01:04:14,240
Mr. Taylor.

1109
01:04:14,273 --> 01:04:16,976
I Know Those Folks
Told You

1110
01:04:17,008 --> 01:04:18,410
Not To Go Out Lookin' For Work,

1111
01:04:18,443 --> 01:04:20,412
But I Have A Few
Painting Gigs,

1112
01:04:20,445 --> 01:04:23,782
And I Could Sure
Use Your Help.

1113
01:04:23,816 --> 01:04:25,852
I Can't Pay You
Mechanic's Salary,

1114
01:04:25,885 --> 01:04:27,387
But It'd
Be Something.

1115
01:04:28,921 --> 01:04:30,256
Appreciate It.

1116
01:04:30,289 --> 01:04:31,724
See You In The Morning.

1117
01:04:31,757 --> 01:04:33,927
Gotta Go
To A Gig Now.

1118
01:04:40,932 --> 01:04:43,902
House Painter.

1119
01:04:47,405 --> 01:04:49,409
[ Noises Behind Door ]

1120
01:05:14,934 --> 01:05:17,202
Hey, Sweetie.
How Was Your Lunch?

1121
01:05:17,235 --> 01:05:20,138
Fine.

1122
01:05:20,171 --> 01:05:23,141
Is Everything Okay, Ruby?

1123
01:05:23,175 --> 01:05:26,144
More Kids Came Back,
Mrs. Henry.

1124
01:05:26,177 --> 01:05:28,447
It's Not My School
Anymore.

1125
01:05:28,481 --> 01:05:31,316
How-- How Do You Know
More Kids Came Back, Ruby?

1126
01:05:31,349 --> 01:05:33,351
I Saw 'Em.

1127
01:05:33,385 --> 01:05:35,354
How Come They're All
In The Class Together

1128
01:05:35,387 --> 01:05:36,956
And I'm Not?

1129
01:05:41,059 --> 01:05:43,395
Um--

1130
01:05:43,429 --> 01:05:45,898
Uh--

1131
01:05:45,930 --> 01:05:48,767
Why Don't You Make
Some More Valentines,
Sweetheart?

1132
01:05:48,800 --> 01:05:52,838
And, Uh-- And I'll Be Back
In Just A Few Moments, Okay?

1133
01:05:52,871 --> 01:05:54,840
Okay.

1134
01:05:54,874 --> 01:05:58,778
There Is No Good Reason
Why She Should Be
By Herself All Day,

1135
01:05:58,811 --> 01:06:03,316
Especially Since The Other
Children Are First Graders
And Right Next Door.

1136
01:06:03,349 --> 01:06:06,119
Miss Spencer Does Not
Want To Teach That Child,

1137
01:06:06,151 --> 01:06:08,521
And Nobody's
Gonna Force Her.

1138
01:06:06,151 --> 01:06:08,521
Fine.

1139
01:06:08,554 --> 01:06:11,923
Then Let Her Children
Come Into Ruby's Class
For Part Of The Day,

1140
01:06:11,956 --> 01:06:13,726
And I'll Teach Them!

1141
01:06:15,327 --> 01:06:17,396
As An Outsider,

1142
01:06:17,429 --> 01:06:20,032
What Makes You
So Concerned?

1143
01:06:22,101 --> 01:06:24,202
Miss Woodmere,

1144
01:06:24,235 --> 01:06:27,939
It Is Cruel
To Isolate A Child.

1145
01:06:27,972 --> 01:06:32,144
Those Children
Are Not Goin'
To Accept Her.

1146
01:06:32,177 --> 01:06:34,012
So You Just Let It Be!

1147
01:06:34,046 --> 01:06:36,215
This School Was Ordered
To Integrate!

1148
01:06:36,247 --> 01:06:38,416
If You Continue
To Separate Ruby,

1149
01:06:38,450 --> 01:06:40,987
You Are Breaking
The Federal Law!

1150
01:06:41,019 --> 01:06:43,088
Shall We Call
Superintendent Redmond

1151
01:06:43,121 --> 01:06:45,257
And Discuss It
With Him?

1152
01:06:52,831 --> 01:06:56,535
Mrs. Spencer?

1153
01:06:52,831 --> 01:06:56,535
Uh-Huh!

1154
01:06:56,568 --> 01:06:59,538
Children!
This Is Mrs. Henry.

1155
01:06:56,568 --> 01:06:59,538
Hello.

1156
01:06:59,572 --> 01:07:02,208
C'mon Now!
Let's All Line Up
Behind Marie.

1157
01:07:02,240 --> 01:07:04,309
We're Gonna Go
Into Mrs. Henry's Class
For A While.

1158
01:07:04,342 --> 01:07:06,411
[ Child ]
Oh, No, Her Class?

1159
01:07:06,445 --> 01:07:09,182
Oh, No!

1160
01:07:06,445 --> 01:07:09,182
[ Barbara ]
This Is Ruby, Everyone.

1161
01:07:09,215 --> 01:07:11,184
Go Ahead.

1162
01:07:11,217 --> 01:07:13,519
Come On. In You Go.

1163
01:07:13,552 --> 01:07:16,088
This Is Ruby.

1164
01:07:16,121 --> 01:07:18,090
Here We Go.

1165
01:07:19,624 --> 01:07:23,929
Duck.

1166
01:07:19,624 --> 01:07:23,929
Ruby's In The Game Too.
No Skipping!

1167
01:07:23,963 --> 01:07:26,298
Duck. Duck.

1168
01:07:26,331 --> 01:07:29,334
Duck.
Goose!

1169
01:07:29,367 --> 01:07:32,003
[ Footsteps ]

1170
01:07:32,037 --> 01:07:34,439
[ Kids Chattering ]

1171
01:07:34,472 --> 01:07:36,942
My Mommy Told Me Not
To Play With You

1172
01:07:36,976 --> 01:07:38,577
Because You're A "Niggah."

1173
01:07:38,610 --> 01:07:40,846
He Not Gonna Go!

1174
01:07:38,610 --> 01:07:40,846
[ Whispering ]
I Don't Want To Play With Her.

1175
01:07:40,880 --> 01:07:43,382
Scott, You're It!

1176
01:07:40,880 --> 01:07:43,382
[ Whispering ] I Don't Wanna
Play With Her, Either.

1177
01:07:43,414 --> 01:07:45,483
Don't You Want
To Play, Scott?

1178
01:07:43,414 --> 01:07:45,483
No.

1179
01:07:45,517 --> 01:07:47,486
C'mon.
It's Fun To Be "It."

1180
01:07:47,519 --> 01:07:49,522
I Don't Wanna Be!

1181
01:07:47,519 --> 01:07:49,522
Come On.

1182
01:07:49,554 --> 01:07:51,623
You Can Do It.

1183
01:07:51,657 --> 01:07:54,494
Stand Up. Let's Go!

1184
01:07:51,657 --> 01:07:54,494
I Don't Wanna Be "It."

1185
01:08:01,333 --> 01:08:05,238
No, Jim Didn't
Hurt My Feelings,

1186
01:08:05,271 --> 01:08:08,641
'Cause If My Mama
Or My Daddy

1187
01:08:08,673 --> 01:08:11,443
Told Me Not
To Play With Someone,

1188
01:08:11,476 --> 01:08:14,246
I Wouldn't, Either.

1189
01:08:14,280 --> 01:08:18,517
Alison Daddy Told Her
Not To Play With Me Too,

1190
01:08:18,549 --> 01:08:22,187
[ Whispering ]
But She Still Does
Sometimes.

1191
01:08:22,220 --> 01:08:25,558
[ Whispering ]
I Won't Tell.

1192
01:08:22,220 --> 01:08:25,558
[ Laughs ]

1193
01:08:25,590 --> 01:08:28,326
Will Your Mom Let
You Have Some Of My Tea?

1194
01:08:28,360 --> 01:08:32,665
It's Special Blend.
Imported From Up North.

1195
01:08:32,697 --> 01:08:37,436
Hmm.
Yeah, I Think That
Would Be A Good Thing.

1196
01:08:37,469 --> 01:08:41,007
It'll Be Just A Moment
While It Brews.

1197
01:08:44,343 --> 01:08:47,479
Ruby,

1198
01:08:47,513 --> 01:08:52,318
Would, Uh-- Would You Be
Disappointed If, Uh,

1199
01:08:52,351 --> 01:08:56,054
My Mommy Said
I Couldn't Have Tea
With You?

1200
01:09:02,561 --> 01:09:05,031
I Would Be Sad,

1201
01:09:05,063 --> 01:09:09,334
'Cause Maybe You
Wouldn't Visit Me Anymore.

1202
01:09:05,063 --> 01:09:09,334
Is It, Uh--

1203
01:09:09,367 --> 01:09:11,370
Is It Lonely For You
At School?

1204
01:09:11,402 --> 01:09:15,007
When I'm By Myself
At Lunchtime.

1205
01:09:15,040 --> 01:09:17,543
Mrs. Henry's Nice.

1206
01:09:17,576 --> 01:09:20,980
But The Other Kids
Don't Play With Me.

1207
01:09:21,013 --> 01:09:25,418
You Know, It-- It's Good
To Know How You Feel, A-And
To Tell Someone, Ruby.

1208
01:09:25,451 --> 01:09:27,954
It'll Make You
Feel Better.

1209
01:09:27,986 --> 01:09:30,255
I'm Certainly Glad
You Told Me.

1210
01:09:30,289 --> 01:09:33,326
Is There Anything
Else That, Uh--

1211
01:09:33,358 --> 01:09:35,327
You Could Do
To Make Yourself
Feel Better,

1212
01:09:35,361 --> 01:09:40,132
Like Cry
Or Laugh Or, Uh--

1213
01:09:40,165 --> 01:09:42,135
Draw With The Crayons?

1214
01:09:44,236 --> 01:09:46,372
Our Tea Is Ready!

1215
01:09:49,241 --> 01:09:50,710
Ah!

1216
01:09:54,245 --> 01:09:56,581
Oh! For Me?

1217
01:10:01,085 --> 01:10:02,354
Mm!

1218
01:10:02,388 --> 01:10:05,058
But We Have To Pray
Before We Eat It.

1219
01:10:07,226 --> 01:10:08,294
Mm.

1220
01:10:08,326 --> 01:10:11,329
God Is Great. God Is Good.

1221
01:10:11,362 --> 01:10:14,200
Now We Thank Him
For This Food.

1222
01:10:14,232 --> 01:10:16,302
In Jesus' Name. Amen.

1223
01:10:16,335 --> 01:10:18,171
Amen.

1224
01:10:24,343 --> 01:10:28,247
Your Daddy Gonna Let
You Be In The Ball Game
Next Time We Play?

1225
01:10:28,280 --> 01:10:30,349
Don't Think So.
Says Colored Folk

1226
01:10:30,382 --> 01:10:32,550
Ain't Got Time
To Be Playin' Games.

1227
01:10:32,584 --> 01:10:35,720
Says You Gotta Work Hard
If You Wanna Have Something
In This World.

1228
01:10:35,754 --> 01:10:37,456
- [ Man ] Alison!
- Uh-Oh.

1229
01:10:37,488 --> 01:10:40,425
Where Are You?

1230
01:10:37,488 --> 01:10:40,425
I'm Comin', Daddy!

1231
01:10:40,459 --> 01:10:42,561
What Did I Tell You?

1232
01:10:42,594 --> 01:10:44,563
You Just March Yourself
On Back Over To That House!

1233
01:10:44,595 --> 01:10:48,233
Lewis,
Ain't No Need
To Holler.

1234
01:10:48,267 --> 01:10:50,269
I Reckon,
We Hear You,
All Right.

1235
01:10:50,302 --> 01:10:51,570
You Know, Bridges,

1236
01:10:51,602 --> 01:10:53,104
'Fo' Your Kid
Went To That School,

1237
01:10:53,138 --> 01:10:55,107
This Neighborhood
Was Doin' Fine.

1238
01:10:55,139 --> 01:10:57,642
But Now We Got Barricades,
Ain't Welcome In Stein's,

1239
01:10:57,675 --> 01:10:59,812
White Folks Up The Street
Lookin' At Us Sideways.

1240
01:10:59,844 --> 01:11:03,382
Now, Colored Folks
Is Talkin' About
Boycottin' Mardi Gras.

1241
01:11:03,415 --> 01:11:05,751
Which Means
My Tavern Ain't Gonna
Do No Business!

1242
01:11:05,784 --> 01:11:07,719
So, If I Wanna Holler--

1243
01:11:07,753 --> 01:11:10,188
Well, You Sure Are Gonna
Hear Me, All Right!

1244
01:11:17,428 --> 01:11:19,398
[ Sighs ]

1245
01:11:41,719 --> 01:11:43,722
Uh!

1246
01:11:41,719 --> 01:11:43,722
[ Laughs ]

1247
01:11:56,535 --> 01:12:00,540
[ Angry Chanting ]
Go Home! Go Home! Go Home!

1248
01:12:06,311 --> 01:12:08,414
Go Home!

1249
01:12:10,148 --> 01:12:13,218
[ Chanting Continues ]

1250
01:12:10,148 --> 01:12:13,218
Ruby, Don't Look.
Hold It, Guys!

1251
01:12:13,251 --> 01:12:16,121
No, Ruby!
Come Back, Sweetie.

1252
01:12:20,325 --> 01:12:22,528
[ Angry Chanting
Continues ]

1253
01:12:29,567 --> 01:12:31,536
But, Honey, I Saw You
Talking To Them.

1254
01:12:31,570 --> 01:12:33,139
Did You Finally
Get Angry With Them?

1255
01:12:33,171 --> 01:12:36,541
Did Ya... Tell 'Em Just
To Leave You Alone?

1256
01:12:36,575 --> 01:12:38,911
No. I Didn't Tell
Them Anything.

1257
01:12:38,943 --> 01:12:42,348
I Didn't Talk To Them.

1258
01:12:38,943 --> 01:12:42,348
But, Ruby.
I Was There.

1259
01:12:42,380 --> 01:12:44,150
I Saw Your Lips Moving.

1260
01:12:44,183 --> 01:12:45,818
I Wasn't Talking To Them.

1261
01:12:45,851 --> 01:12:48,254
I Was Praying For Them.

1262
01:12:49,487 --> 01:12:50,856
Praying For Them?

1263
01:12:50,888 --> 01:12:55,160
Yes. I Pray For Them
Every Day In The Car.

1264
01:12:55,193 --> 01:12:58,229
But I Forgot That Day.

1265
01:12:58,263 --> 01:12:59,564
Oh.

1266
01:13:01,366 --> 01:13:03,569
What Prayer Did You Say?

1267
01:13:05,704 --> 01:13:10,342
Please, God,
Forgive These People.

1268
01:13:10,375 --> 01:13:13,779
Because Even If They Say
Those Mean Things,

1269
01:13:13,812 --> 01:13:16,247
They Don't Know
What They're Doing.

1270
01:13:16,281 --> 01:13:19,251
So You Can Forgive Them.

1271
01:13:19,284 --> 01:13:23,589
Just Like You Did Those Folks
A Long Time Ago

1272
01:13:23,621 --> 01:13:26,358
When They Said
Terrible Things About You.

1273
01:13:31,662 --> 01:13:36,302
We Used To Have
One Painting Of Jesus
On The Wall.

1274
01:13:36,335 --> 01:13:38,404
Somebody Stole It.

1275
01:13:39,638 --> 01:13:40,773
Know What?

1276
01:13:40,805 --> 01:13:42,775
I'm Going To Put
My Paintings

1277
01:13:42,808 --> 01:13:44,944
Up On The Wall Now.

1278
01:13:42,808 --> 01:13:44,944
Okay.

1279
01:13:46,378 --> 01:13:48,414
Hey, Little Boy!

1280
01:13:48,446 --> 01:13:50,516
[ Laughs ]
Whee!

1281
01:13:50,549 --> 01:13:52,751
[ Cielle ]
Carl, Don't Jump
On Miss Jane Like That!

1282
01:13:52,784 --> 01:13:57,522
Get Off There!

1283
01:13:52,784 --> 01:13:57,522
He's Okay. He's Okay.
Just Wanted To--

1284
01:13:57,555 --> 01:14:00,326
[ Laughing ]

1285
01:14:00,358 --> 01:14:02,961
Okay. Where Do You
Want To Put Them?

1286
01:14:00,358 --> 01:14:02,961
Right There.

1287
01:14:02,995 --> 01:14:06,799
All Right.

1288
01:14:02,995 --> 01:14:06,799
So, Doc, How's
My Little Girl Doin'?

1289
01:14:06,831 --> 01:14:09,602
[ Sighs ]
Okay.

1290
01:14:09,634 --> 01:14:13,371
You Know,
You Comin' Here,

1291
01:14:13,405 --> 01:14:15,608
Payin' Attention
To Her Like That,

1292
01:14:15,641 --> 01:14:18,410
Listenin' To Her--
That Makes Her Feel
Real Special.

1293
01:14:18,442 --> 01:14:20,878
Dr. Coles, Would You
Like Something To Drink?

1294
01:14:20,911 --> 01:14:23,848
Ah, That Sounds Great.
Thanks.

1295
01:14:23,882 --> 01:14:27,786
Here We Go.
C'mon, Baby.
C'mon, Carl.

1296
01:14:27,818 --> 01:14:31,389
And, Uh,
It's Bob, Please.

1297
01:14:27,818 --> 01:14:31,389
Bob.

1298
01:14:32,557 --> 01:14:36,762
I, Uh, Appreciate
Your Kind Words Very Much.

1299
01:14:36,794 --> 01:14:42,267
But, Uh, I Think
What Makes Ruby Feel
So Special Is...

1300
01:14:42,300 --> 01:14:45,437
You And Your Family
And...

1301
01:14:45,469 --> 01:14:48,940
Something Greater Than,
Than All Of Us.

1302
01:14:48,973 --> 01:14:53,878
[ Sighs ]
All This Time I Wondered
What Makes Her So Strong.

1303
01:14:53,911 --> 01:14:56,714
Don't Be Too Hard
On Yourself, Doc.

1304
01:14:56,747 --> 01:14:59,751
I Think There're Things
We're Not Supposed
To Figure Out

1305
01:14:59,785 --> 01:15:01,987
Till The Time Is Right.

1306
01:15:02,019 --> 01:15:03,289
Know What I Mean?

1307
01:15:05,089 --> 01:15:08,793
Uh-Huh.
Yeah. Huh.

1308
01:15:08,826 --> 01:15:10,061
I Mean,
Look At These Pictures.

1309
01:15:10,094 --> 01:15:11,629
Remember All The Ones
She Did

1310
01:15:11,662 --> 01:15:13,365
With The Pink Crayons?

1311
01:15:13,397 --> 01:15:15,800
Pink And Deformed.

1312
01:15:13,397 --> 01:15:15,800
[ Laughs ]
Yeah.

1313
01:15:15,834 --> 01:15:19,571
She's Certainly Wearing Out
The Brown Ones Now, Huh?

1314
01:15:19,603 --> 01:15:21,840
[ Sighs ]
Now, That's Progress.

1315
01:15:19,603 --> 01:15:21,840
Here We Are!

1316
01:15:23,842 --> 01:15:27,478
Wow.
What's That?

1317
01:15:23,842 --> 01:15:27,478
That's Gumbo.

1318
01:15:27,512 --> 01:15:29,615
Looks Great!

1319
01:15:27,512 --> 01:15:29,615
Mmm, Try It!

1320
01:15:31,650 --> 01:15:34,920
Mmm!

1321
01:15:31,650 --> 01:15:34,920
[ Laughs ]

1322
01:15:37,488 --> 01:15:39,023
<I>[ Dr. Coles On Tape Recorder ]
And So, I Learned

1323
01:15:39,057 --> 01:15:40,893
<I>That A Family And A Child
Under Great Stress And Fear

1324
01:15:40,925 --> 01:15:42,561
<I>Could Show Exquisite
Dignity And Courage

1325
01:15:42,594 --> 01:15:44,863
<I>Because Of Their Moral
And Religious Values,

1326
01:15:44,896 --> 01:15:46,932
<I>And Because They Had
A Definite Purpose

1327
01:15:46,964 --> 01:15:49,668
<I>In What They Were
Trying To Accomplish.

1328
01:15:49,701 --> 01:15:51,670
<I>This Purpose
Made Them Resilient.

1329
01:15:51,702 --> 01:15:54,406
<I>I Couldn't Figure Out The
Source Of This Resilience

1330
01:15:54,438 --> 01:15:56,575
<I>Because I Had Only Worked
With Well-To-Do Children

1331
01:15:56,607 --> 01:15:58,409
<I>Who Really Had Nothing
To Work Hard For--

1332
01:15:58,442 --> 01:16:01,446
<I>No Reason Driving Them
To Accomplish Anything.

1333
01:16:01,479 --> 01:16:03,949
<I>So Now I See That
The Issue Is Not Stress

1334
01:16:03,982 --> 01:16:06,452
<I>But Stress
For What Purpose.

1335
01:16:06,485 --> 01:16:08,420
<I>Having Something
To Believe In

1336
01:16:08,452 --> 01:16:10,555
<I>Protected Ruby
From Psychiatric Symptoms

1337
01:16:10,589 --> 01:16:12,925
<I>And Gave Her A Dignity
And A Strength

1338
01:16:12,958 --> 01:16:17,062
<I>That Is Utterly Remarkable.

1339
01:16:18,597 --> 01:16:21,800
"So All We Could Do
Was To Sit, Sit, Sit."

1340
01:16:21,833 --> 01:16:24,036
She Is A Good Teacher.

1341
01:16:24,068 --> 01:16:28,039
My Kids Can't Read
That Well Yet.

1342
01:16:28,072 --> 01:16:30,675
Miss Woodmere?
From The Janitor.

1343
01:16:28,072 --> 01:16:30,675
Oh, Thank You.

1344
01:16:30,709 --> 01:16:33,812
Uh-Huh.

1345
01:16:30,709 --> 01:16:33,812
[ Bell Ringing ]

1346
01:16:33,844 --> 01:16:37,449
Lunchtime. Walk!
C'mon. Let's Walk.

1347
01:16:37,482 --> 01:16:39,985
Walk!

1348
01:16:43,888 --> 01:16:48,426
[ Clears Throat ]
There Have Been Mice
And Cockroaches In Here,

1349
01:16:48,460 --> 01:16:50,830
And The Janitor Needs
To See Why.

1350
01:16:54,031 --> 01:16:56,034
[ Cabinet Door Slams ]

1351
01:17:04,709 --> 01:17:07,046
What's All This?
Oh!

1352
01:17:10,682 --> 01:17:12,651
[ Miss Woodmere ]
Ugh!

1353
01:17:15,519 --> 01:17:18,089
[ Miss Woodmere ]
Disgusting!

1354
01:17:15,519 --> 01:17:18,089
[ Thunderclap ]

1355
01:17:25,095 --> 01:17:27,066
[ Sighs ]

1356
01:17:30,669 --> 01:17:35,974
Tsk.
I'm Not Angry
With You, Honey.

1357
01:17:36,007 --> 01:17:41,647
I'm Just Very Concerned
That You're Not Eating
Your Lunches.

1358
01:17:41,679 --> 01:17:46,150
I Mean, You're So Tiny
At It Is.

1359
01:17:46,183 --> 01:17:49,821
I Been Eatin' More
Than I Used To, Mrs. Henry.

1360
01:17:49,854 --> 01:17:51,889
Really.

1361
01:17:51,923 --> 01:17:55,995
But I Don't Like
What My Mama Makes Me
All The Time.

1362
01:18:02,601 --> 01:18:05,470
[ Giggling ]

1363
01:18:06,905 --> 01:18:09,875
[ Laughing ]
Want Some More?

1364
01:18:06,905 --> 01:18:09,875
That's For You.

1365
01:18:12,878 --> 01:18:14,213
Okay, Ruby, Here's A Test

1366
01:18:14,245 --> 01:18:16,147
To See How Well
You've Learned This Year.

1367
01:18:18,049 --> 01:18:21,019
Now, Honey,
You Take Your Time,
And You Do Your Best.

1368
01:18:28,559 --> 01:18:32,063
What's In The Box?

1369
01:18:28,559 --> 01:18:32,063
It's A Surprise.
That's What's In The Box.

1370
01:18:32,097 --> 01:18:33,898
What's In The Box?

1371
01:18:33,932 --> 01:18:35,800
He-He-Here We Go. Ho!

1372
01:18:35,834 --> 01:18:37,936
Look! I Draw Good Too!

1373
01:18:37,969 --> 01:18:39,571
Mine, Look At Mine!

1374
01:18:39,603 --> 01:18:41,240
You Two Get In The House!

1375
01:18:41,272 --> 01:18:44,242
Wow! Here. I'll Look
At Those Later. Okay?

1376
01:18:44,276 --> 01:18:47,112
I'm Sorry
About That, Bob.

1377
01:18:44,276 --> 01:18:47,112
Aw, That's Okay.

1378
01:18:47,144 --> 01:18:50,516
Hey.
You Wanna Play A Game?

1379
01:18:47,144 --> 01:18:50,516
What You Paint, Baby?

1380
01:18:50,549 --> 01:18:52,985
Okay?
This Is Your Classroom.

1381
01:18:53,018 --> 01:18:54,920
And Let's Say
That These Are, Uh,

1382
01:18:54,952 --> 01:18:56,621
You And The Other Students.

1383
01:18:56,655 --> 01:18:57,822
And I Was Wondering
If Maybe

1384
01:18:57,856 --> 01:18:59,525
You Could Tell Me
Something About Them.

1385
01:18:59,558 --> 01:19:02,628
And, Who They Are
And-- And What They're Like.

1386
01:19:07,132 --> 01:19:09,968
This One's Marie.
She's Nice.

1387
01:19:10,000 --> 01:19:14,239
Her Daddy's
A Minister.

1388
01:19:10,000 --> 01:19:14,239
Oh, Yeah?

1389
01:19:15,307 --> 01:19:18,644
This One's Scott.
He's Okay.

1390
01:19:18,677 --> 01:19:20,978
But He Doesn't
Really Like Girls.

1391
01:19:21,012 --> 01:19:22,981
Uh-Huh.

1392
01:19:23,013 --> 01:19:27,018
[ Dog Barking ]

1393
01:19:27,052 --> 01:19:30,755
This Is Jimmy.
He Used To Be Bad.

1394
01:19:30,789 --> 01:19:33,925
Now He Plays
Okay Sometimes.

1395
01:19:33,959 --> 01:19:36,961
But, Then, He Remembers
I'm Colored...

1396
01:19:36,995 --> 01:19:38,997
And Gets Bad Again.

1397
01:19:39,030 --> 01:19:42,834
How Exactly
Does He Act
When He Gets Bad?

1398
01:19:42,866 --> 01:19:44,302
He Pushes Me.

1399
01:19:44,335 --> 01:19:47,638
He Calls Me
Mean Things.

1400
01:19:47,671 --> 01:19:50,241
What Do You Do, Ruby,

1401
01:19:50,275 --> 01:19:51,943
When He Calls You
Mean Things?

1402
01:19:51,977 --> 01:19:56,247
Do You Get Angry And
Do Mean Things Back?

1403
01:19:56,281 --> 01:20:01,053
No. I Used To Be Bad
When Someone Did
Mean Things To Me.

1404
01:20:01,085 --> 01:20:05,122
At Church, I Heard
When Someone Is Bad,

1405
01:20:05,156 --> 01:20:08,994
God Makes A Bad Thing
Come Back On That Person.

1406
01:20:09,027 --> 01:20:11,797
So, I Don't
Do It Anymore.

1407
01:20:11,830 --> 01:20:14,800
I Want A "Co-Cola."

1408
01:20:11,830 --> 01:20:14,800
Okay.

1409
01:20:14,833 --> 01:20:17,068
You Want One?

1410
01:20:14,833 --> 01:20:17,068
Yeah.

1411
01:20:19,137 --> 01:20:21,273
Hey, Daddy!

1412
01:20:19,137 --> 01:20:21,273
Hey, Doc!

1413
01:20:21,305 --> 01:20:24,610
Cielle's Teachin'
Your Wife To Make Gumbo.

1414
01:20:21,305 --> 01:20:24,610
Uh-Oh.

1415
01:20:24,643 --> 01:20:26,845
Man, It's
Gonna Be A While.

1416
01:20:26,878 --> 01:20:29,113
[ Chuckles ]

1417
01:20:26,878 --> 01:20:29,113
Feel Like Takin' A Walk
When You Get Done?

1418
01:20:29,147 --> 01:20:32,718
- Sure. Great.
- All Right.

1419
01:20:46,031 --> 01:20:48,000
[ Sighs ]

1420
01:20:52,202 --> 01:20:54,205
[ Knocking ]

1421
01:20:56,907 --> 01:20:58,876
Mrs. Stein.

1422
01:20:56,907 --> 01:20:58,876
This Is For
Your Family.

1423
01:20:58,910 --> 01:21:01,179
[ Abon ] Things Finally
Calmin' Down Around Here.

1424
01:21:01,211 --> 01:21:04,182
[ Dr. Coles ]
Yeah.

1425
01:21:01,211 --> 01:21:04,182
Well, Thank You.

1426
01:21:04,214 --> 01:21:09,253
♪ I Said Tell Me, Darlin'
Why You Got To Be So Mean ♪

1427
01:21:10,421 --> 01:21:12,691
Hey, Abon!

1428
01:21:12,723 --> 01:21:15,092
♪ But Where I Come From ♪

1429
01:21:15,125 --> 01:21:18,829
♪ You're Still
The Prettiest Thing
I've Ever Seen ♪

1430
01:21:18,862 --> 01:21:21,066
Now, Go On,
Blow Your Horn, Boy!

1431
01:21:24,369 --> 01:21:27,106
♪ [ Continues ]

1432
01:21:29,441 --> 01:21:32,110
Who Got The Medals?

1433
01:21:32,143 --> 01:21:34,113
Holden.

1434
01:21:35,813 --> 01:21:38,150
I Ever Tell You
I Got Me A Purple Heart?

1435
01:21:38,183 --> 01:21:40,852
Ah, No, But Janie Told Me.
How'd You Get It?

1436
01:21:40,884 --> 01:21:44,155
Got Wounded In Korea
Savin' A White Soldier.

1437
01:21:44,188 --> 01:21:45,923
Mmm.

1438
01:21:45,956 --> 01:21:49,994
So You Shed Blood

1439
01:21:50,027 --> 01:21:52,296
For A Country That Doesn't
Really Allow You

1440
01:21:52,330 --> 01:21:55,800
To Enjoy The Freedom
You Fought To Maintain.

1441
01:21:56,901 --> 01:22:01,005
That Can't Feel Good.

1442
01:21:56,901 --> 01:22:01,005
Nope.

1443
01:22:01,039 --> 01:22:06,010
That's Why
I Ain't Never Put Much Faith
In Integration, You Know.

1444
01:22:06,044 --> 01:22:08,847
I Mean, Even In The War,
Fightin' Side By Side,

1445
01:22:08,879 --> 01:22:10,981
We Were Still Colored,
They Were Still White.

1446
01:22:11,014 --> 01:22:15,454
Risked My Life For 'Em,
And... We Still Didn't Mix.

1447
01:22:17,421 --> 01:22:19,191
[ Laughs ]
We Sure Ain't Never...

1448
01:22:19,223 --> 01:22:22,760
Hung Out Together
Or Nothin'.

1449
01:22:22,794 --> 01:22:25,798
Before I Met Ruby,
I Never Thought
About Segregation.

1450
01:22:26,830 --> 01:22:29,366
You Didn't Have To.

1451
01:22:29,400 --> 01:22:32,036
- It's Gotta Make You
Angry, Huh?
- [ Sighs ]

1452
01:22:35,473 --> 01:22:38,977
No.
Not No More.

1453
01:22:39,009 --> 01:22:41,379
[ Laughs ]
Don't Do Me No Good.

1454
01:22:42,781 --> 01:22:46,051
You Know, Doc,
Believe It Or Not,

1455
01:22:46,084 --> 01:22:49,054
I Learn A Lot
From Watching My Ruby.

1456
01:22:49,086 --> 01:22:50,755
Oh,
I Definitely Believe It.

1457
01:22:50,789 --> 01:22:52,458
[ Laughs ]
She's A Great Teacher.

1458
01:22:54,325 --> 01:22:56,762
[ Woman ]
I'm So Happy This Year
Is Comin' To A Close.

1459
01:22:56,794 --> 01:22:58,796
You Have No Idea.

1460
01:23:00,197 --> 01:23:04,469
Miss Woodmere, May I Have
Ruby's Test Scores, Please?

1461
01:23:17,447 --> 01:23:19,950
Oh!
Oh, This Is Wonderful!

1462
01:23:19,983 --> 01:23:21,887
I Knew She Would Do Well.

1463
01:23:21,919 --> 01:23:24,088
Her Test Scores
Are Incredible!

1464
01:23:24,121 --> 01:23:26,857
Hmm, That's Exactly
What I Thought.

1465
01:23:26,891 --> 01:23:29,460
That's Why I'm Lowering Them
To More Accurately Reflect

1466
01:23:29,494 --> 01:23:32,497
A True Assessment
Of Her Ability.

1467
01:23:37,902 --> 01:23:40,305
What?

1468
01:23:40,338 --> 01:23:42,340
Well, She's Been
Privately Tutored
The Whole Year Through,

1469
01:23:42,372 --> 01:23:44,843
Which Makes Her Scores
Inaccurate.

1470
01:23:44,875 --> 01:23:49,313
She's Had Special Attention
The Other Children
Just Did Not Have.

1471
01:23:49,347 --> 01:23:52,951
[ Woman ]
That's True.

1472
01:23:49,347 --> 01:23:52,951
That's What This Is.

1473
01:23:52,983 --> 01:23:55,821
You're Upset
Because She Did Better
Than The Other Children.

1474
01:23:55,853 --> 01:23:59,824
Her Scores Are Too High,
And I'll Change Them
As I See Fit.

1475
01:23:59,857 --> 01:24:02,393
Then I Would Like
To Discuss It
With The Principal.

1476
01:24:02,427 --> 01:24:04,563
I Already Have.

1477
01:24:04,595 --> 01:24:10,302
She Did The Work By Herself,
So The Scores Are Accurate.

1478
01:24:10,335 --> 01:24:13,038
The Only Reason
She Was Privately Taught

1479
01:24:13,071 --> 01:24:15,340
Is Because You Would Not
Put Her With Other Children.

1480
01:24:15,372 --> 01:24:17,442
You Tried To Mix
Those Children,

1481
01:24:17,474 --> 01:24:20,111
And You Failed, Didn't You?

1482
01:24:20,143 --> 01:24:22,179
They Didn't Accept Her.

1483
01:24:20,143 --> 01:24:22,179
That's Not True.

1484
01:24:22,213 --> 01:24:23,314
- Oh?
- They're Children.

1485
01:24:23,348 --> 01:24:26,084
They Don't Care
What Color She Is.

1486
01:24:26,116 --> 01:24:28,320
It Is Only Their Parents

1487
01:24:28,352 --> 01:24:31,889
And Ignorant People
Who Teach Them To Hate.

1488
01:24:33,357 --> 01:24:36,994
If You Are Unhappy Here,
Please Don't Come Back.

1489
01:24:37,027 --> 01:24:39,930
- Miss Woodmere!
- Shut Up!

1490
01:24:39,964 --> 01:24:42,367
What About The Children,
Miss Woodmere?

1491
01:24:43,468 --> 01:24:46,905
Do They Mean
Anything To You?

1492
01:24:46,937 --> 01:24:50,908
You May Dismiss
The Hard Work
Of One Little Girl,

1493
01:24:50,942 --> 01:24:54,546
But There Will Be
Other Little Girls
And Boys.

1494
01:24:54,579 --> 01:24:58,215
The Country Is Changing,
Miss Woodmere,

1495
01:24:58,249 --> 01:25:00,586
Whether You Like It
Or Not.

1496
01:25:05,223 --> 01:25:09,394
[ Footsteps Receding ]

1497
01:25:09,427 --> 01:25:13,999
That Woman Worked
Her Behind Off This Year,
Miss Woodmere.

1498
01:25:14,031 --> 01:25:15,666
She Spent Nearly Every
Minute Of Every Day

1499
01:25:15,700 --> 01:25:19,204
Bein' Dedicated
To Her Job!

1500
01:25:19,236 --> 01:25:21,272
And Your Job,
Miss Woodmere,

1501
01:25:21,305 --> 01:25:24,576
Is To Support
All Your Teachers,

1502
01:25:24,608 --> 01:25:26,644
Not To Sabotage Them.

1503
01:25:29,947 --> 01:25:31,950
Huh.

1504
01:25:35,253 --> 01:25:36,388
All Right, Carl, Come On Now!

1505
01:25:36,420 --> 01:25:38,956
Keep Your Eye On It. Get Your
Grip On The Bat. Swing!

1506
01:25:38,990 --> 01:25:41,459
C'mon!
Hit It Carl!

1507
01:25:38,990 --> 01:25:41,459
That's Right, Carl!

1508
01:25:41,491 --> 01:25:44,396
You Gonna Knock It
Over The Fence!
[ Laughs ]

1509
01:25:55,106 --> 01:25:57,342
Hey, Abon.
How About That Carl, Huh?

1510
01:25:57,375 --> 01:26:01,345
- C'mon, Carl,
Hit It! Hit It! Hit It!
- A Real Little Slugger.

1511
01:26:01,379 --> 01:26:03,448
And Ruby's Been Playin'
Real Good Too.

1512
01:26:03,481 --> 01:26:05,583
Been Coachin' 'Em?

1513
01:26:05,616 --> 01:26:09,487
Nah, No-- She--
She Don't Need My Help.
She Just Got Natural Talent.

1514
01:26:09,519 --> 01:26:13,191
- C'mon, Carl! Hit It!
C'mon, Carl!
- Give Me The Bat. It's Mine!

1515
01:26:13,223 --> 01:26:16,527
Aw, Abon, Maybe She Gets
Some Of It From You.

1516
01:26:16,561 --> 01:26:20,499
Whatever It Is,
We All Real Proud Of Her
Around Here.

1517
01:26:26,036 --> 01:26:30,541
Anybody? Is That All?
Anybody Want Anymore?
We Got Popsicles.

1518
01:26:30,575 --> 01:26:33,077
- You Want A Popsicle?
- Popsicle?

1519
01:26:33,111 --> 01:26:35,546
Oh, Boy!

1520
01:26:35,580 --> 01:26:37,515
What Kind You Got?

1521
01:26:37,548 --> 01:26:40,385
Gimme The Bat.
Gimme It!

1522
01:26:37,548 --> 01:26:40,385
Uh! Uh-Uh!

1523
01:26:40,418 --> 01:26:42,353
Give Me The Bat.

1524
01:26:40,418 --> 01:26:42,353
[ Ruby ]
You Know What?

1525
01:26:42,387 --> 01:26:45,055
What?

1526
01:26:42,387 --> 01:26:45,055
I'm Gonna Have
A Birthday Party Soon.

1527
01:26:45,089 --> 01:26:47,092
No!

1528
01:26:45,089 --> 01:26:47,092
And You And Mrs. Coles
Can Come To It.

1529
01:26:47,125 --> 01:26:49,127
You Know What?
We'll Be There.

1530
01:26:49,160 --> 01:26:51,196
Yeah?

1531
01:26:49,160 --> 01:26:51,196
Yeah!

1532
01:26:51,228 --> 01:26:53,231
Tell Me About
Your Picture.

1533
01:26:55,767 --> 01:26:58,202
This Is You
And Mrs. Coles.

1534
01:26:58,236 --> 01:27:01,673
That's Mrs. Henry,
And That's The Broyards.

1535
01:27:01,705 --> 01:27:04,342
And Why'd You Put Us
In There?

1536
01:27:01,705 --> 01:27:04,342
'Cause I Like You Now.

1537
01:27:06,710 --> 01:27:09,246
Who's This Here?

1538
01:27:06,710 --> 01:27:09,246
That's Jimmy.

1539
01:27:09,280 --> 01:27:11,648
He's Says He's Gonna Be
My Friend Now,

1540
01:27:11,682 --> 01:27:14,786
Even Though His Mom
Told Him Not To Be.

1541
01:27:14,818 --> 01:27:17,621
He Doesn't Call Me
Bad Names Anymore.

1542
01:27:17,655 --> 01:27:19,057
That's Good.

1543
01:27:23,326 --> 01:27:26,463
I Think People Are Happier
When They Make Friends.

1544
01:27:26,496 --> 01:27:29,401
What Do You Think?

1545
01:27:29,433 --> 01:27:31,468
[ Sighs ]

1546
01:27:31,501 --> 01:27:35,539
I Think You've Been
A Great Teacher.
That's What I Think.

1547
01:27:35,572 --> 01:27:37,541
Can I Have A Hug,
Teacher?

1548
01:27:39,143 --> 01:27:42,113
[ Laughs ]
Oh, Ruby!

1549
01:27:53,257 --> 01:27:55,626
[ Children Shouting ]

1550
01:28:01,499 --> 01:28:04,269
C'mon!

1551
01:28:04,302 --> 01:28:05,804
Barbara, I'm Sorry
We Didn't Get

1552
01:28:05,836 --> 01:28:07,671
To Know Each Other
Better This Year.

1553
01:28:20,718 --> 01:28:22,620
Get On!

1554
01:28:22,652 --> 01:28:24,856
I Think What You Did
Was The Right Thing.

1555
01:28:24,888 --> 01:28:27,458
And I Think
You Did It Really Well.

1556
01:28:29,360 --> 01:28:32,697
Believe It
Or Not, That...

1557
01:28:32,729 --> 01:28:36,233
Means A Lot To Me.

1558
01:28:36,267 --> 01:28:38,135
Maybe Next Year,
If You Get Ruby

1559
01:28:38,169 --> 01:28:41,238
Or Someone Like Her
In Your Class...

1560
01:28:41,272 --> 01:28:44,142
You'll Be Able
To Do The Same.

1561
01:28:46,477 --> 01:28:49,613
<I> [ Narrator ] In 1995,
Ruby Bridges Established

1562
01:28:49,647 --> 01:28:52,117
<I> The Ruby Bridges
Educational Foundation,

1563
01:28:52,150 --> 01:28:53,785
<I> Which Seeks To Build
An Understanding

1564
01:28:53,818 --> 01:28:58,322
<I> Of Cultural Diversity
Within Public Schools
Across The Nation.

1565
01:28:58,356 --> 01:28:59,724
<I> Under Her Leadership,

1566
01:28:59,757 --> 01:29:02,227
<I> The Growth And Success
Of This Foundation

1567
01:29:02,259 --> 01:29:03,294
<I> Continues To Prove

1568
01:29:03,327 --> 01:29:05,662
<I> That The Sacrifices
Her Family Made

1569
01:29:05,696 --> 01:29:07,099
<I> Were Not In Vain.

